# .cppcheck-suppress -- Cppcheck suppression list for messageEngine
# Policy: CLAUDE.md S9.1 Tier 2b
# Format: <id>[:<file>[:<line>]]
# Each suppression must have a justification comment on the preceding line.
#
# Usage: cppcheck --suppressions-list=.cppcheck-suppress ...
#
# IMPORTANT: Adding a suppression is a deviation from the MISRA / Power of 10
# standard. Every entry here must be reviewed during inspection (CLAUDE.md S12)
# and logged in docs/DEFECT_LOG.md with a WAIVE disposition.

# System headers are not analysed; missing-include noise for <cassert>, <cstdint> etc.
# is expected and not a project defect.
missingIncludeSystem

# Cppcheck emits this when a suppression in this file does not match any finding
# in the current run. Suppress to avoid false failures as code evolves.
unmatchedSuppression

# POSIX socket API returns int; Cppcheck flags the signed/unsigned comparison in
# fd range checks (fd >= 0). This is intentional and correct POSIX idiom.
# Deviation: MISRA C++:2023 Rule 5.0.4 (implicit integral conversions) -- waived
# for POSIX socket fd comparisons only. Logged: DEFECT_LOG.md INSP-000-1 (pending).
# signConversion:src/platform/SocketUtils.cpp

